What is single page appliocation?  A single-page application (SPA) is a web application or website that fits on a single web page with the goal of providing a more fluid user experience similar to a desktop application. This is accomplished by sending only the data to be displayed in order to display and interact with the content, without requiring multiple pages to load. SPAs usually use AJAX technologies and sometimes WebSockets to facilitate interaction and dynamic content within the page.
